transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hello, thank you for calling Viagra, how can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Yes, is this customer service also?

Speaker 1: Yes, how can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Okay, I just called and somehow we got cut off.

Speaker 1: But what happened is I got some of these old pills

Speaker 2: and I want to order some new AGB.

Speaker 1: And when I ordered them, I got some again, which were the old ones.

Speaker 2: And the girl said, well, she sent me an email over here

Speaker 1: where to send the old ones back.

Speaker 2: And she said, you just can't go online, you have to call and get the new AGBs.

Speaker 1: Okay, yes, so for the AGB you want to purchase 25 pills, correct?

Speaker 2: Yes, the new ones.

Speaker 1: They sent me just the old ones that they always have.

Speaker 2: And she said, no, you've got to call.

Speaker 1: And she said she was going to send me some of the AGB, 100 mg,

Speaker 2: but I never got them, so something must have went wrong in the system.

Speaker 1: Okay, so do you want 50 milligrams or 100 milligrams?

Speaker 2: 100 of the new AGB, yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, so 25 pills, 100 milligrams.

Speaker 2: I think 25, I just wanted to try them.

Speaker 1: How much is 25?

Speaker 2: It's 25 pills for $99.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Let me just have a 25.

Speaker 1: And you should have my address and everything.

Speaker 2: Okay, and John, is your shipping address still the same,

Speaker 1: 1002 Hathaway, Mesquite, Nevada, 89027?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, and can I charge the visa ending in 6520?

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: May I place that order for you?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And I'm going to Europe in about three days, four days,

Speaker 2: so I don't know if it will be here in time or not.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: I was able to successfully place in that order for you,

Speaker 1: so you should be receiving it within the next three to five business days,

Speaker 2: okay?

Speaker 1: Very good.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: I appreciate that.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
